.\" termin.al-name: login
.\" termin.al-usage: login
.\" termin.al-summary: Authenticate with GitHub.
.TH LOGIN 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
login \- Authenticate with GitHub.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
login
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Identifies the authentication command name, but host authentication is unavailable in the current browser demo. No GitHub or other authentication flow begins.
.SH FAILURES
Every invocation returns the stable command-rejected diagnostic:
.PP
Authentication is unavailable until the host authentication work is implemented.
.PP
Arguments do not change this outcome.
.SH NOTES
No credential, token, cookie, session or browser-storage value is created. This manual makes no promise about a future authentication protocol.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ login
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
logout(1), whoami(1), cv(1)
